de.adorsys.datasafe.types.api.callback

Interface SoftwareVersionCallback

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Callback, ResourceWriteCallback
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface SoftwareVersionCallback
extends ResourceWriteCallback
    Called when file is persisted using software-versioning to tell callee what was the version id assigned to the file (happens when OutputStream is closed and response from storage is received). NOTE: It will get called only if version was assigned and only by software-versioning layer.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void handleVersionAssigned(String version)
      Handles assigned version to the file
